Title: Arbitrary file write with vcrtrace
Class: security
Compatible: compat
Component: checks
Date: 1745999709
Edition: cre
Level: 1
Version: 2.2.0p42

Previous to this Werk it was possible to inject arguments to the commandline of some checks and special agents.
If the option <code>--vcrtrace</code> was injected the http traffic was dumped into a file given via this parameter.
The path was not validated.

This vulnerability was identified in a commissioned penetration test conducted by PS Positive Security GmbH.

<em>Affected Versions</em>:

LI: 2.4.0 (beta)
LI: 2.3.0
LI: 2.2.0
LI: 2.1.0 (EOL)

<em>Vulnerability Management</em>:

We have rated the issue with a CVSS Score of 8.7 High (<code>CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N</code>) and assigned <code>CVE-2025-1712</code>.
